SECTION 1: SYSTEM ARCHITECTURE OVERVIEW
The Core Principle
Every framework in the Architect Advantage ecosystem is connected. They are not a collection of separate tools — they are one integrated system designed to move a founder from reactive growth to intentional architecture. The AE Ladder diagnoses where the business is. The Growth Mastery System designs where it goes next. The Dimensions, Pillars, Capability Areas, and Checkpoints measure what must evolve and prove that it has. The Universal Frictions reveal where design energy is needed. Founder Evolution tracks the human arc running alongside all of it.

The Hierarchy at a Glance
THE AE LADDER — The diagnostic framework. Maps agency maturity across 5 stages. Answers: Where are you, and why does it feel this way?
THE GROWTH MASTERY SYSTEM (GMS) — The design framework. Maps the pathway of progression across 4 Horizons. Answers: What do you do about it, and how do you architect the next level?
THE 5 DIMENSIONS — The universal organizing structure shared by both frameworks. Define what must evolve for the business to mature. Run vertically through every stage and every horizon.
THE 9 PILLARS — The functional leverage areas nested within the Dimensions. Define through what mechanisms growth is achieved. Used as the organizing layer for content development — not always explicitly named in coaching, but always operating underneath.
THE 25 CAPABILITY AREAS — The specific competencies within each Pillar that can be independently evaluated and developed. The primary unit of measurement and scoring in the assessment architecture.
THE 125 CHECKPOINTS — The observable, verifiable proof points within each Capability Area. Define what it looks like when a capability has been built and is functioning at a given stage. Stage-appropriate — what counts as proficient at Rising is different from what counts at Driving.
THE 3 UNIVERSAL FRICTIONS — Cross-cutting signals that appear at every stage and every horizon. Indicate where design energy is needed. Each maps to a cluster of 3 Pillars.
FOUNDER EVOLUTION — A parallel arc, separate from the AE Ladder. Tracks both the mindset shift (Operator → Owner → Architect) and the structural involvement shift (Operator → Investor). Not stage-locked — a founder can evolve mentally faster than the business allows structurally.

