The Relationship Between the AE Ladder and the GMS
These two frameworks are designed to work in tandem, not in isolation.
The AE Ladder creates awareness — it places the agency within a maturity stage based on the pattern of complexity across all 5 Dimensions. It gives founders language for what they're experiencing and a realistic picture of what needs to evolve.
The GMS creates a design pathway — it defines what must be built, strengthened, and institutionalized at each Horizon to move the agency forward. The 4 Horizons (Model, Scale, Systems, Exit) map directionally to the AE Ladder stages but are not identical to them. The Ladder identifies altitude; the GMS builds the architecture to climb higher.
Together: The Ladder tells you your stage. The GMS tells you your next design challenge.

